The paper discusses a framework for Planning while Learning, which involves an agent achieving a goal in an environment with partial knowledge. This topic is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG), as the agent is learning from the environment to make decisions. The paper also discusses the tractability of plan-design processes, which is related to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper emphasizes the role of off-line plan-design processes, which is related to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
